The paper is about a neural reading comprehension model that combines a multi-type answer predictor and a multi-span extraction method for dynamically producing one or multiple text spans. This involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer science sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The model also involves ranking arithmetic expression candidates, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the model's performance is evaluated using a dataset of text passages and questions, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) since text recognition and understanding is a key component of many computer vision applications.
